    {
      "id": "p004",
      "index": 4,
      "source": "Across comparable generations, operating costs per GPU are broadly similar because chip TDP is the dominant driver of TCO for operating costs. This goes up as you move from H100s to GB300s, given chip TDP double, driving up operating costs per hour per GPU",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
